summary: The module extracts, aggregates, and formats health‑system interaction (HSI) data from model runs, computes various metrics such as event counts, resource fractions, and time shares, and produces a series of descriptive figures and tables that illustrate treatment distributions, appointment usage, healthcare‑worker time allocation, bed occupancy, and related squeeze factors for calibration analysis.
business_intent: To provide detailed, visual and tabular summaries of health‑system resource use and treatment pathways that support model calibration, validation, and stakeholder understanding of system performance under different scenarios.
